The paper deals with the problem of fair allocation of resources among multiple agents, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of graphs to model the relationships between agents suggests a possible connection to social network analysis (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents a new protocol for cake cutting, which involves discrete and bounded algorithms, indicating a possible connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
